firejail (0.9.7-testing1) baseline; urgency=low
  * This is a test release, tracking some compilation problems on OpenSUSE
  * Implemented nowrap mode for firejail --list command option
  * User privilege level locking set as default. The feature requires a Linux kernel 3.5 or newer
  * Added --unlock option to allow user privilege escalation on Linux kernels 3.5 or newer
  * Added pid support for firemon
  * Added firemon --top option
  * bugfixes

-- netblue30 <netblue30@yahoo.com>  Fri, 4 Jun 2014 07:35:00 -0500
  
firejail (0.9.6) baseline; urgency=low

  * Mounting tmpfs on top of /var/log, required by several server programs
  * Server fixes for /var/lib and /var/cache
  * Private mode fixes
  * csh and zsh default shell support
  * Chroot mode fixes
  * Added support for lighttpd, isc-dhcp-server, apache2, nginx, snmpd,

